[read linear_algebra_ftl/D_kernel.ftl]

Let K denote a field.

Axiom neg_kern. Let V,W be vector spaces over K. Let f < Hom(K,V,W).
Let u,v < V. Let f[u] = f[v]. Then u -{V} v << Ker(f).

Axiom kern_zero_inj. Let V,W be vector spaces over K. Let f < Hom(K,V,W).
Assume Ker(f) = {0{V}}. Then f is injective.

Axiom kern_subspace. Let V,W be vector spaces over K.
Let f < Hom(K,V,W). Then Ker(f) is a subspace of V over K.